cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses energy consumption in distributed computing systems and proposes energy-aware scheduling algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper involves dynamic voltage-frequency scaling, which is a control technique used to manage power consumption in computer systems. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of DVFS capability incorporated in commodity processors. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper discusses scheduling algorithms that aim to improve energy efficiency while maintaining performance. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the development and evaluation of scheduling algorithms.
